# Cleaner Code with Destructuring

Instead of writing `props.name`, you can destructure the props object directly in the function parameter.

```jsx
function Greeting({ name, age }) {
  return <h1>{name} is {age} years old</h1>;
}
```

You can also set **default values** for props using default parameters:

```jsx
function Button({ text = 'Click me', color = 'blue' }) {
  return <button style={{ backgroundColor: color }}>{text}</button>;
}
```

slides.codeSnippet:
function Product({ name, price, inStock = true }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h3>{name}</h3>
      <p>Price: ${price}</p>
      {inStock ? <p>In stock</p> : <p>Out of stock</p>}
    </div>
  );
}

// Usage
<Product name="Laptop" price={999} />
<Product name="Phone" price={699} inStock={false} />

